{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"All subtasks complete: self-recursion detection, small-value probing, iterative deepening, and mutual recursion support. 168 tests pass, clippy clean.","closed_at":"2026-02-26T04:18:16Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"219a3e7bdce210929c5ee6533cbec0321d6146d411de46a8e463af9d6a6ba6be","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:37:19Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Currently CallGraph::test_order() rejects cycles (including self-recursion) with CallGraphError::Cycle. This means recursive functions cannot be tested compositionally. We need to handle self-recursion and mutual recursion as special cases of compositional testing using iterative deepening with behavior map bootstrapping.\n\n## Strategy\n\n1. Detect self-recursive and mutually-recursive functions from the call graph\n2. Identify base-case branches (branches that don't contain recursive calls)\n3. Solve for base-case inputs first to build an initial BehaviorMap\n4. Mock self-calls using the BehaviorMap built so far, iteratively deepening\n5. Stop when coverage stabilizes or max depth is reached\n\n## Edge cases\n\n- No obvious base case (always self-calls) — need max-depth cutoff as safety net\n- Base case depends on external state — fall back to random probing\n- Higher-order recursion (function passed as argument calls the original) — out of scope initially\n\n## Subtasks\n\n- Detect self-recursive functions and identify base-case branches\n- Small-value probing for quick base-case discovery\n- Iterative deepening via self-call mocking\n- Mutual recursion support","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-2lz","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":""