{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"All generators implemented in input_gen.rs: Option/Result (with present/ok flags), Complex/Rational/Range numerics, Closure (canned variants), Iterator (value arrays), and all domain-specific types (Money, SemVer, Email, Color, GeoPoint, Locale, MimeType). Full dispatch, export formatting, and reconstruction in both frontends.","closed_at":"2026-02-27T05:40:07Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"7d01c8c1769e92445e96b8f700daf0502653f00e071cf3afc63e2ef4c4b41740","created_at":"2026-02-27T04:49:04Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Support for functional types that can be passed as inputs: generators, reconstruction, and tests.\n\n## What\n1. Core generators (input_gen.rs):\n   - generate_closure: Small set of canned function variants that frontends know how to construct:\n     - \"identity\": returns its first argument\n     - \"constant\": always returns a fixed value (include the value in wire format)\n     - \"thrower\": always throws an error\n     - \"noop\": returns undefined/nil\n     Wire: {\"__complex_type\": \"closure\", \"variant\": \"identity\"} or {\"__complex_type\": \"closure\", \"variant\": \"constant\", \"value\": 42}\n\n   - generate_iterator: Generate a small array of values and let the frontend wrap in its iterator protocol\n     Wire: {\"__complex_type\": \"iterator\", \"values\": [1, 2, 3]}\n\n2. TS reconstruction:\n   - closure: switch on variant to return appropriate function: (x) =\u003e x, () =\u003e value, () =\u003e { throw new Error() }, () =\u003e {}\n   - iterator: values[Symbol.iterator]() or generator function\n\n3. Go reconstruction:\n   - closure: Generate Go function values (func(x interface{}) interface{} { return x })\n   - iterator: Not natively applicable in Go (no iterator protocol). Skip or use channel/slice.\n\n## Solver\nTier 3 — not representable symbolically. Fuzzing with the canned variants provides enough coverage to test callback-taking functions.\n\n## Note\nThis is lower priority because callback-heavy code is harder to test concretely. The main value is being able to explore higher-order functions at all rather than failing on Unknown type.\n\n## Files\n- shatter-core/src/input_gen.rs\n- shatter-ts/src/reconstruct.ts\n- shatter-go/reconstruct/reconstruct.go","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-3d5","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":4,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Functional types end-to-end (Closure, Iterator)","updated_at":"2026-02-27T05:40:07Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"All acceptance criteria already met: all 3 example languages have .shatter/config.yaml, inputs/ directories, labeled candidates, global defaults, per-function overrides, skip directives, and glob patterns.","closed_at":"2026-03-03T00:10:25Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"fdfc0bfc4f17ca734ded3983c1547eba420cb26e0c334697f40bd150a848d859","created_at":"2026-02-27T02:33:55Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Context\n\nDepends on str-9js (candidate inputs and .shatter/ convention). Once the convention is implemented, the examples should demonstrate it.\n\n## Problem\n\nThe current examples in `examples/typescript/` and `examples/go/` are flat collections of standalone functions. They don't resemble real projects — no package structure, no configuration, no candidate inputs. Users looking at the examples won't see how to set up .shatter/ for their own projects.\n\n## What to Do\n\n### Restructure examples as realistic mini-projects\n\nEach example language directory should look like a small real project:\n\n```\nexamples/\n  typescript/\n    package.json\n    tsconfig.json\n    .shatter/\n      config.yaml               # project-level defaults + per-function overrides\n      inputs/\n        classifyNumber/\n          candidates.json       # known edge cases for this function\n        validateToken/\n          candidates.json       # realistic auth payloads\n        global/\n          candidates.json       # common boundary values\n    src/\n      01-arithmetic.ts\n      02-strings.ts\n      ...\n  go/\n    go.mod\n    .shatter/\n      config.yaml\n      inputs/\n        ClassifyNumber/\n          candidates.json\n    ...\n```\n\n### Config examples should demonstrate\n\n- Global defaults with reasonable values\n- Per-function overrides showing both higher limits (complex functions) and lower limits (simple ones)\n- `skip: true` for at least one function\n- Candidate inputs that include: typical values, boundary values, regression cases (labeled)\n- A glob pattern override (e.g., `\"*_test.go\":` skip)\n\n### Candidate input examples should demonstrate\n\n- Inputs matching each function's actual parameter types\n- Labels explaining why each candidate matters (\"boundary: zero\", \"regression: overflow\", \"production: typical payload\")\n- Both function-scoped and global candidates\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Each example language has a `.shatter/config.yaml` and at least one `inputs/` directory\n- `shatter run examples/typescript/` picks up the config and candidates automatically\n- The examples serve as copy-paste templates for users setting up their own projects\n- README or comments in config.yaml explain the convention for new users","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-3dq","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":3,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Add .shatter/ configuration to examples as realistic project templates","updated_at":"2026-03-03T00:10:25Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
