{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"3cbf47bd6b8182f65455afb1bf4694cb47da9cfa2468f733686084ef7aaaf7c1","created_at":"2026-03-05T02:59:37Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"buildSymExprWithFlow tracks the last assignment to a variable on the concrete execution path. This loses precision for conditional reassignment:\n\n  let x = a;\n  if (cond) x = b;\n  use(x)  // symbolic value is just 'b' if that branch was taken, 'a' otherwise\n\nWith SSA, this becomes x₂ = φ(x₀, x₁) which maps to ite(cond, b, a). Z3 handles ite natively, so the solver could reason about both branches simultaneously.\n\nCurrent behavior: correct for the concrete path taken (concolic sees the right value), but the symbolic expression doesn't capture the relationship to the branch condition. When the solver negates a downstream constraint, it doesn't know that x's value depends on cond.\n\nImplementation:\n- Track assignment versions per variable in the data flow map (x_0, x_1, ...)\n- At control flow merge points (after if/else, switch), insert phi entries: x_merge = ite(branch_condition, x_then, x_else)\n- Emit the ite SymExpr so Z3 can reason about both possibilities\n\nApplies to all frontends:\n- TS: let/var reassignment inside if/else/switch blocks\n- Go: any variable reassignment inside if/else/switch\n- Rust: less common due to immutability defaults, but let mut reassignment in branches applies. Deferred until execute lands.\n\nKey files: shatter-ts/src/instrumentor.ts, shatter-go/instrument/","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-4kop","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":n