{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":"2026-02-27T15:42:18Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"343493cf49cc2fd9ceca9ada10e3daa794bbed2cb6dd299b47122e79b96c02d8","created_at":"2026-02-27T05:08:58Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Add a new TypeInfo::Opaque { label: String } variant for runtime resource types that cannot be meaningfully constructed for testing (sockets, file descriptors, database connections, streams, channels). Distinct from Unknown (type couldn't be resolved) and Complex (type is known and constructible).\n\n## What\n1. shatter-core/src/types.rs — add Opaque { label: String } variant to TypeInfo enum. Add has_opaque(\u0026self) -\u003e bool recursive walker and find_opaque_label(\u0026self) -\u003e Option\u003cString\u003e helper that walk into Array elements, Object fields, Union variants, Nullable inner.\n2. shatter-core/src/input_gen.rs — add Opaque { .. } arm to generate_random_value() returning Value::Null (caller should never reach this for opaque types, but safe fallback).\n3. shatter-core/src/reporter.rs — add Opaque { label } arm to type display.\n4. protocol/schemas/type-info.schema.json — add opaque kind with required label: string field.\n\n## Why\nFunctions accepting runtime resources (net.Socket, *os.File, chan int) currently get random garbage inputs via Unknown, crash immediately, waste cycles, and produce noisy output. A distinct Opaque variant lets the system cleanly identify and skip these functions.\n\n## Tests\n- Round-trip serde for Opaque { label: \"net.Socket\" }\n- Nested: Opaque inside Array, Object, Nullable\n- has_opaque() returns true for direct and nested Opaque, false for all-primitive trees\n- find_opaque_label() returns first label found in tree","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_m