{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":"2026-03-03T19:16:55Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"abe23eb43af7d571f8707c94b62ed513d0e4fd0d512fe9f4a15141b74593a850","created_at":"2026-03-03T15:53:25Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Extend ErrorInfo with a structured error_category enum so frontends classify errors at capture time using language-level signals.\n\nProposed enum values: validation, runtime, infrastructure, unknown\n\nFrontend classification heuristics:\n- TS: custom error subclasses or names matching *Validation*/*Invalid* → validation. TypeError/ReferenceError/SyntaxError → runtime. Timeout → infrastructure.\n- Go: known panic types and timeout → infrastructure. Custom error types implementing specific interfaces → validation. Generic panics → runtime.\n- Rust: similar mapping from error type hierarchies.\n\nAlso classify based on caught/uncaught status (caught errors more likely intentional) and stack depth (shallow throws in the target function more likely validation than deep library errors).\n\nImplementation scope:\n1. Add error_category: Option\u003cString\u003e to ErrorInfo in shatter-core/src/protocol.rs and execution_record.rs\n2. Update protocol JSON schemas in protocol/schemas/\n3. Implement classification in each frontend (TS executor.ts, Go executor.go, Rust handler.rs)\n4. Add round-trip serialization tests for the new field\n5. Update exploration report to surface the category\n\nComplements but does not depend on branch-path correlation (option 2). The frontend does NOT have branch context — classification is purely from error type, caught/uncaught status, and stack depth.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-6dlt","is_template":0,